  "original_title": "Sri Lanka\u2019s private bus owners warn drivers to refrain from fuel hoarding, overcharging",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka\u2019s private bus owners warn drivers to refrain from fuel hoarding, overcharging",
      "author": "Dulya de Silva",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka\u2019s Private Bus Owners\u2019 Association (SLPBOA) President warned that legal action would be taken against drivers who hoard fuel or overcharge consumers, and requested that the public report such behaviour, as the ongoing fuel crisis makes traveling a luxury for most commuters.",
        "\u201cDrivers have become thugs because there is a great demand. If the demand was reduced, we could avoid this situation,\u201d said SLPBOA President Gemunu Wijeratne, addressing the media on 17 July.",
        "\u201cIf any driver charges extra, you can file a police report, and if the allegations are proved true then their license will get revoked.\u201d",
        "Wijeratne stated that the same would happen to drivers who hoard fuel.",
        "\u201c[SLPBOA] will not get behind these people. Their licenses will be revoked and they can be put under arrest.\u201d",
        "In a bid to reduce fuel hoarding, the Power and Energy Ministry of Sri Lanka introduced a fuel token system. Hoarding has become a serious issue, and sources say that Sri Lanka\u2019s fuel consumption has significantly increased after the shortage began.",
        "Wijeratne added that passengers should not get onto overcrowded buses, or engage in risky behaviour while travelling.",
        "\u201cWe see people going on the roofs of the buses. If you fall, you will end up breaking your neck, so don\u2019t do dangerous things like that.",
        "But with only 1000 to 3000 buses available island-wide every day, commuters do not have the luxury of waiting for a less crowded bus.",
        "Commuters are also unable to find taxis that are unavailable despite the exorbitant fares they are desperate enough to pay to travel. (Colombo/Jul17/2022)"
      ],
